members.member:
Fields that are not part of the BO4E-definition are stored in a element, that is accessable under the key defined in userPropertiesName.
This JObject representing a Messlokation
{ "boTyp": "MESSLOKATION", "versionStruktur": 1, "messLokationsId": "DE123...", "irgendwas unbekanntes": "xyz" }
is mapped to
{ "boTyp": "MESSLOKATION", "versionStruktur": 1, "messLokationsId": "DE123...", "userProperties": { "irgendwas unbekanntes": "xyz" } }
This keeps the Business Object simple but allows for user specific arguments beyond the BO4E standard to be passed along.

member.example:
Marktlokation malo = ... some initialisation code ...;
malo.GetBoKeyNames()

[ "marktlokationsId" ]


Marktteilnehmer : Geschaeftspartner
{
    [BoKey(true)]
    public string rollencodenummer;
}

We don't want the Marktteilnehmer BO to inherit the keys like name1 etc. 
from the Geschaeftspartner object because the rollencodenummer is a better ID.

example.code:
public class Ansprechpartner : BusinessObject
